// Global css variables import
@import 'codification'

// body
//     font-family: $fontContent
//     background-color: $colorPrimary
// Test code for @import link in sass - it was way easier that I thought

// LOGO DESIGN
.logo
    display: flex
    background-color: darken($colorSecondary, 40)
    height: 40vw
    width: 40vw
    flex-direction: column
    align-items: center
    justify-content: center
    border-top-left-radius: 3rem
    border-bottom-right-radius: 3rem
    margin: 1rem
    padding: 0.5rem

#symbolBorder
    border: 2px solid $colorPrimary
    border-radius: 50%
    width: 80%
    height: 80%
    display: flex
    justify-content: center
    align-items: center
        //! STILL NEED TO CENTER DAT THANG
#symbol
    font-size: 4rem
    color: $colorFourth

#name
    font-family: $fontTitles
        // This part i'm proud of ... Looked up text gradient and found
        // https://cssgradient.io/blog/css-gradient-text/
        // But it's out of date and non standard, so converted it to supported code
    // background: linear-gradient(to right, $colorPrimary, $colorSecondary) //Could also be background image
    // background-clip: text
    color: $colorFourth//transparent

#mainMenu
    display: none
    flex-direction: column
    background-color: lighten($colorFifth, 10)
    height: 100vh
    padding: 2rem
    align-items: center
    justify-content: space-around
    ul
        list-style: none


.mainMenuLinks
    position: relative
    display: block
    background-color: darken($colorSecondary, 40)
    width: 80vw
    height: 2.5rem
    margin: 1rem
    // https://stackoverflow.com/questions/21444096/how-to-center-text-inside-anchor-tag used and adapted
    text-align: center
    line-height: 2.5rem
    border-radius: 3px
    .anchorGradient
        font-family: $fontContent
        // background: linear-gradient(to right, $colorPrimary, $colorSecondary) //Could also be background image
        // background-clip: text
        color: $colorFourth//transparent
    *
        padding: 0
    img 
        position: absolute
        transform: scale(0.08) rotate(-0.1turn)
        top: -218px
        left: -169px

#sideBarWrapper
    position: fixed
    right: 0
    top: 0
    
#bigBar
    background-color: lighten($colorFifth, 2)
    height: 100vh
    width: 3vw
    border-top-left-radius: 1rem
    border-bottom-left-radius: 1rem
    position: relative
    opacity: 0.85
    
#buttonBar
    position: absolute
    top: 10%
    right: -3rem
    transform: translate(-50%,-50%)
    background-color: lighten($colorFifth, 0)
    height: 5rem
    width: 5rem
    border-radius: 2rem 0 0 2rem
    display: flex
    font-size: 3rem
    justify-content: center
    align-items: center


// Large devices (laptops/desktops, 1200px and up) */
@media screen and (min-width: 1200px)
    #mainMenu
        display: flex
        height: 4.5vh
        flex-direction: row
        justify-content: space-between
        ul 
            display: flex
        img 
            position: absolute
            transform: scale(0.07) rotate(-0.15turn)
            top: -218px
            left: -386px
    .logo
        height: 50px
        width: 50px
        border-top-left-radius: 1rem
        border-bottom-right-radius: 1rem
        #name
            display: none
    #bigBar
        display: none
    .mainMenuLinks
        width: 120px
    #symbol
        font-size: 0.8rem
